Public education systems do not offer comprehensive, nurture sexuality education.[27] Schools also do not follow up in addition to educating on menstruation/vaginal hygiene and sexual and reproductive health and rights and including human rights of sexuality.[28]

Contraceptive abuse contributes to a lack of sexual and reproductive health and rights (SRHR) supports and information.[29]

Cultural beliefs about masculinity and power (shame and stigma) encourage men to beat their wives, though it punishable by law.
